description: Key Lime Juice is a tart, acidic liquid that is made from the juice of the key lime fruit. Key limes are smaller and more tart than traditional limes, and are a staple ingredient in many culinary traditions, particularly in the Caribbean and South Florida. Key Lime Juice is used in a variety of dishes and drinks, including marinades, sauces, pies, and cocktails. Its tart flavor adds a bright and tangy touch to recipes, and its acidity makes it a great ingredient for balancing flavors and tenderizing meats.
name: Key Lime Juice

description:
Oranfrizer blood orange juice is obtained from the juicing of the Sicilian Tarocco, Moro and Sanguinello orange varieties. The citrus groves located on the slopes of Etna, the highest active volcano of Europe, are exposed to a micro-climate unique in the world which yields warmth to the plants during the day and goes down to temperatures near zero at night.
This temperature range is the secret behind the extraordinary pigmentation of the blood oranges that Oranfrizer Juice squeezes. Each litre of fresh-squeezed Red Orange juice there is the juice of about 2.6 kg of Tarocco, Moro and Sanguinello blood oranges ripened and processed by us.
name: 100% Sicilian Blood Orange Juice

description:
The juice of the lemon is composed of about 5% citric acid, with a pH of around 2.2, giving it a sour flavor profile. Its distinctive taste makes lemon juice a key ingredient in food and beverages. Lemons were commercially grown first in Europe, in Genoa, in the 15th century and then introduced into the Americas by Christopher Columbus. Spanish conquest throughout the New World helped spread lemon seeds. In the 19th century, lemons were increasingly planted in Florida and California. description: Twisted Alchemy cold-pressed moro blood orange juice mixer is a carefully pressed purely from the Moro variety from Italy, and Sanguinello of Spain. The blood orange likely originated from a hybrid of pomelo and tangerine fruits in the mid-18th century in the southern Mediterranean. The dark blood-like maroon color comes from the antioxidant Anthocyanin, which spreads from the peel to the center flesh of each fruit. Sweeter than other species of oranges and with a slight tart, raspberry-like taste, our 100% cold-pressed moro blood orange juice compliments anything from dark bourbons to light bubbly wines, and also makes a dashing garnish to finish off any cocktail.
name: 100% Blood Orange Juice

description: Filthy Olive Brine is the liquid that accompanies olives and is often used as a flavoring or seasoning in cocktails or recipes. This particular brine is made by Filthy Foods and is designed to have a rich, salty flavor with a slightly sour taste. It is made from a blend of high-quality olives and is packaged in a bottle for easy use. The brine is often used to add a savory depth to martinis, bloody marys, and other cocktails. It can also be used to add flavor to marinades, dressings, and other recipes.

description: Our Club Soda has a silky smooth texture created by using the finest spring water (which has a low mineral content) and a high level of carbonation; it has no aroma so it can more effectively bring to life the flavours of the premium spirit it's being mixed with. Our Club Soda is our simplest product. After our natural spring water is carbonated with lots of very fine bubbles, we add Bicarbonate of Soda, which is used to add a minerality that enhances naturally occuring flavours in the spirits it's paired with.

description:
Beautifully crafted Chenin/Chardonnay Still White Wine from South Africa. <0.5% ABV

Produced using 55% Chenin Blanc and 45% Chardonnay grapes harvested from dry-land farmed vineyards in the Western Cape region. The vineyards are strategically planted on south-west facing slopes to capture cool breezes from the Atlantic Ocean and cold Benguela current. Deep soils from decomposed granite, clay rich, with good drainage.

With 14 days fermentation at 14-15Â°C, the grapes and juice are handled reductively to prevent oxidation and lock in fruitiness. The wine is left on lees for 2 months to add complexity. The wine is then dealcoholized by way of a gently spun cone technology. This is done under vacuum and at low temperature to ensure that the wine retains its distinctive body, color and flavor.
name: Dealcoholized Blanc

description:
FERAGAIA is the moment you step off the path. A balanced blend of wild flavours. A complexity that invites you to pause. To reconnect. To appreciate the people around you and the ground beneath your feet. Distilled to be different.
Here's to your original free spirit. Feragaia was founded in 2019 with a vision to challenge the apologetic nature of alcohol-free drinks, with a truly confident alcohol-free spirit that isnâ€™t trying to mimic anything and stands as a drink in its own right. The original free spirit combines authentic originality with the rich distilling heritage of Scotland. Made from 14 land & sea botanicals that were carefully identified for their flavor profiles and wild earth properties. Its refreshing depth of flavor is a layered journey through wild earth. From the land, the freshness of lemon verbena and blackcurrant leaf brings with it a resilience for the â€˜always onâ€™ modern age. From the sea, nutrient rich Sugar Kelp gives body and breadth whilst promoting inner renewal. And finally, a long finish from spiced botanicals like pink peppercorn, brings a sense of grounding and calm.
name: Feragaia Non-Alcoholic Spirit

description: Coconut milk is a creamy and flavorful liquid made from the meat of coconuts. It is a popular ingredient in many cuisines, particularly in Southeast Asian and Caribbean dishes. The milk is made by grating the meat of a mature coconut and blending it with water, then straining the mixture to remove any remaining bits of coconut. Coconut milk can be used in a wide variety of dishes, from curries and soups to smoothies and baked goods.

description: Our Club Soda has a silky smooth texture created by using the finest spring water (which has a low mineral content) and a high level of carbonation; it has no aroma so it can more effectively bring to life the flavours of the premium spirit it's being mixed with. description: This culinary grade matcha powder is beloved not only for its striking jade green color, but also for its versatility in the kitchen. Made by grinding green tea leaves into a delicate powder, this second harvest matcha offers a deep, earthy flavor with just a mild undertone of bitterness. Originating in Japan, matcha not only lends itself to luxurious hot and iced lattes but also decadent dessert items. Pair with white chocolate and try it out in fudge, cheesecake, brownies, and beyond!

description: Harney and Sons Green Tea Citrus is a blend of green tea with a touch of lemongrass, lemon verbena, and spearmint. The result is a refreshing and flavorful tea with a bright citrus aroma and a smooth, delicate flavor. The tea is made with natural ingredients and is free from artificial flavors and additives. It is packaged in a 20-count tin, with each tea bag individually wrapped to preserve freshness and flavor. This tea can be enjoyed hot or iced, and is a great choice for tea lovers who enjoy a light and refreshing taste with a citrus twist.

description: A barista quality chai concentrate.  Make the perfect chai latte that is just lightly-sweetened yet perfectly balanced. Brewed in small-batches with single origin & direct trade spices. Ground fresh and slow steeped. Notes of organic black tea, cardamom, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and black peppercorn in every sip.  Quality matters. Our beverages are made with the best ingredients selected for their naturally sweet qualities so we add less sugar. Balancing sweet and spice allows our ingredients to shine. To make a chai latte, Mix equal parts Dona concentrate and milk. Heat, steam or pour over ice.

description: Sustainable Packaging: Open Water uses sustainable packaging made of 100% recyclable BPA-free aluminum. Our 16-ounce refillable canned aluminum bottles get recycled more often than any other beverage container material including plastic, glass, and even cartons. Aluminum is also infinitely recyclable, which means it can be recycled over and over without losing quality or volume. Even our cap is made of aluminum! Clean, Pure Taste: Our ultra-purified canned water has a balanced pH and goes through a multi-step purification system. We then add plenty of electrolytes for a clean, balanced taste. Climate Neutral Certified: We are the first bottled water company to go Climate Neutral, which means that we are measuring, reducing, and offsetting all of the carbon emissions that we create as a company, from powering our teamâ€™s computers to producing our bottles and cans.
